This project started as a fork of fatx-rs by Joshua Reisbord
(https://github.com/joshuareisbord/fatx-rs) and is independently
maintained as a personal variant. The FATX/XTAF filesystem
implementation traces back to that work; subsequent additions —
title catalog (merged Xbox 360 + Original Xbox sources), on-demand
STFS resolution, profile gamertag decryption, slot-aware folder
display, TUI-first workflow, and scope simplification — are original
to xtafkit.

